      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To remove a stubborn, dried coffee stain from your light grey rug, first mix a solution of warm water and a few drops of mild dish soap. Gently dab the stain with a clean cloth soaked in the solution, working from the outside in to prevent spreading. After blotting, rinse with a little water and let the area air dry completely. If the stain persists, you might try a small amount of white vinegar mixed with water, but always test any cleaner on an inconspicuous spot first. Never rub the stain, as this will push the coffee deeper into the fibers.",
